##Dr Li Wenliang's last 40 days

Weixin caijingEleven

The function introduction by "CAIJING" Magazine Company Industry Report team to create, discuss the success or failure of the enterprise, explore the rise and fall of the industry, promote sunshine business

There are no heroes who fall from the sky, only mortals who rise to the occasion, one netizen wrote. The young doctor, who has since died, is a reminder to those still fighting the epidemic that the battle is still hard

The season | text

Image courtesy of the web

At 3:48 a.m. on February 7,2020, "Our ophthalmologist, Li Wenliang, died at 2:58 am on February 7,2020, after an unsuccessful attempt to rescue him from the pneumonia epidemic caused by COVID-19 infection, " Wuhan Central Hospital said on its official Weibo Account

Screenshot from Weibo, Wuhan Central Hospital

February 7,13:02 p.m, "With the approval of the Central Committee, the State Commission for Discipline Inspection decided to send an investigation team to Wuhan, Hubei Province, to conduct a comprehensive investigation into the issues reported by the public concerning Dr. Li Wenliang, " the commission's website said

Li Wenliang, 34. He is the father of two children, a five-year-old and a pregnant woman who is less than six months old. On December 30,2019, he stumbled upon a possible outbreak of pneumonia with a new type of viral infection, so he put out a small-scale alert on the wechat group of medical professionals, urging them to "take precautions. ". The optimistic young man didn't realize he was entering his final 40 days.

Although Li Wenliang is an ophthalmologist, the message he warned about on the wechat group was quickly spread by screenshots. The next day he was interviewed by the hospital leadership, 4 days later, he signed a letter of caution with the police, agreed not to spread "rumors. ".

A colleague of Li's said that most of the doctors at the hospital had only spoken, not written, to alert colleagues and family members to take precautions, and that Li should be the only doctor in the hospital who had been "admonished. ".

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Photo: Dr. Li Wenliang

"Admonition" after the end, Li Wenliang returned to work as an ophthalmologist, inadvertently contact with infected patients. According to the doctor, Li Wenliang was among the first doctors in his hospital to be infected. Most of the doctors had masks ready at the time, but "I didn't expect it to be so contagious. ". Today, Li Wenliang's immediate boss, the head of the Ophthalmology Department, is still in the intensive-care unit.

Around January 10, Li Wenliang presented with cough and fever. Li later said in an interview that he was "skeptical" that the virus would not spread from person to person.

At the time, experts from the National Health Commission were unsure whether the virus was transmitted from person to person. Li's suspicions and warnings were later vindicated.

In an interview with CCTV on January 20, Zhong Nanshan, a respiratory specialist, said the COVID-19"definitely transmits from person to person. ". At that time, Li Wenliang's parents have been diagnosed, Li Wenliang symptoms themselves more than a week, has done three nucleic acid test paper tests, two showed "negative" , one showed "positive" , the final diagnosis on February 1.

People familiar with Li Wenliang said the Liaoning Native, who graduated from the Medical College of Wuhan University, was an ordinary man who loved fried chicken and instant noodles and star-chasing dramas. Because he is not good at worldly wisdom, he went to school in Wuhan from Northeast China. After graduation, he first went to Xiamen to work for three years, and then returned to Wuhan. He is expecting his second child this year.

Even after he was diagnosed with a coronavirus infection, he remained optimistic. His favorite TV lead character left a message on his Weibo, and he replied looking forward to seeing the sequel. In an interview with Caixin, he said it was not important to be rehabilitated after being admonished. "A healthy society should not have only one voice. ".

As of 1500 hours on February 7,2020, the COVID-19 had confirmed 31,224 people, 637 had died and 1,606 had been cured, according to public figures. Behind these numbers are ordinary people like Li Wenliang.

"It's more than grief now, " said a doctor at the Central Hospital in Wuhan, who burst into tears on the phone. "What would you do if your savior died? ". Some on the front line want Feb. 6 to be designated Dr. Li's anniversary, the doctor said. "Remember, it's not Feb. 7, it's Feb. 6, " the doctor said.

"If I had a chance to see him yesterday, I would tell him that you can go in peace, " said another doctor at Wuhan Central Hospital who is familiar with Li Wenliang. If we live, we'll drink wine and worship our brothers every year."

"wouldn't give up hope. "

"His condition has always been quite serious, " said one of Li's colleagues. Summing up the information, Li Wenliang developed cough symptoms on January 10, and then began to feel fever and nausea. Around January 15, Li was admitted to the intensive-care unit of Wuhan Central Hospital. He did three nucleic acid test paper test, the results showed two negative and a positive, February 1, Li Wenliang confirmed.

Li's condition began to deteriorate on February 5. At 10:14 on February 6, several experts came to the Department of Critical Care of Wuhan Central Hospital for a consultation with Li Wenliang.

Six minutes later, Li Wenliang was given a blood gas analysis, an arterial blood draw and an injection of hormones. Look at the Wuhan Central Hospital to Li Wenliang medication records: He was already in a critical condition.

Li also spoke to a friend on Feb. 6, saying he was chest tight, out of breath and had an oxygen saturation of 85, according to the Economic Observer. People reported that on the afternoon of February 6, Li Wenliang was transferred from the Nanjing Road Hospital area of Wuhan Central Hospital to the Houhu hospital area. According to Li's classmates, Li was in poor condition and therefore needed an ECMO, however, because the Central Hospital did not have the equipment in the Nanjing Road Park, Li Wenliang had to be transferred to the back Lake Hospital area.

The yaxin hospital confirmed that the ECMO device that saved Li Wenliang was borrowed by Li Wenliang's colleagues from the Yaxin Hospital, which is more than 10 kilometers away. There were no other ECMO devices available in Li's Houhu Hospital district at the time.

According to various sources, around 1900 hours on the night of February 6, Li Wenliang was pushed into the emergency room. At 21:18 that night, medical records showed that Li Wenliang was given an injection of adrenaline, which, according to professionals, usually indicates that the patient's heart might have been very weak or even stopped. The records also show that at 21:33 p.m. , the doctor performed an intubation and was treated with an ECMO artificial lung.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Li Wenliang's medical records dated February 6

"By 9:30 pm, Li Wenliang had lost his basic vital signs and was not responding to the intubation, " said a person close to Li's doctor.

According to a transcript of the chat, Yang, a suction physician at Wuhan Central Hospital, said he was willing to give his name as proof that the doctors had pressed on Li's chest for three hours before they began treating him with an ECMO.

At about 22 p.m. on February 6, news of Li Wenliang's death first broke. "Dr. Li Wenliang died at 21:30 on February 6, " Weibo user "Dr. Do" said in a 22:52 post, dr Syzygium Aromaticum, a public account on Wechat, was also deleted at around 2200 hours after he tweeted "Dr. Li Wenliang of Wuhan died in vain. ".

These claims were broken by a number of internal voices from the Central Hospital in Wuhan. According to multiple sources, after Li's heart stopped that night, doctors performed CPR on him, followed by artificial lung ECMO. Around 22 p.m. that night, Li still had weak vital signs.

"The human body is a very sophisticated instrument, and it's very difficult to get everything right, " said Shen Jun, assistant director of the Wuhan University's Emergency Medical Center and director of Emergency Surgery. He explained that ECMO is a substitute for heart and lung function, and that a person who is temporarily without heart and lung function can use Ecmo to maintain blood and oxygen supply to his other organs without immediate multiple organ failure.

"But in that case, the machine has to be used to its fullest extent. You don't need a heart or a lung, you need a machine to replace it, your vital signs are stable, your organs are functioning normally, " Shen Jun said. Shen Jun and his team had previously used ECMO to resuscitate a newly crowned patient.

At about 23pm on February 6, news of Li Wenliang's death came out for the second time. "At 22:57, Dr. Li Wenliang removed the ECMO, the death, " Weibo User Tan Fei said.

At 00:38 on February 7, the official Weibo Account of Wuhan Central Hospital said that Li Wenliang was "critically ill and under all-out rescue efforts. " A visiting nurse who had entered and left the emergency room said that he could not make it, but that he was still being treated inside, the Caixin reporter saw at the scene.

At around the same time, a person close to Li said the hospital had not yet issued a death notice to his family, who were indeed being treated with an ECMO, "but there is virtually no chance of recovery. "

At this time although already passed midnight, many people still on the social platform for Li Wenliang blessing, expecting the miracle to appear. A Central Hospital medical staff said that before 1 a.m. on February 7, another colleague in the rescue of Li Wenliang, "everyone refused to give up the last glimmer of hope. ".

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Taken outside the rescue room of Li Wenliang, Wuhan Central Hospital

A doctor at Wuhan Central Hospital said Li Wenliang's medical records were still available in the system before 2 a.m. on Feb. 7, but they were no longer displayed after 2 a.m.

At 3:48 a.m. on February 7, news of Li Wenliang's death broke for the third time. "We deeply regret and mourn the death of Li Wenliang at 2:58 a.m. on February 7,2020, after all efforts to revive him failed, " the official Weibo Account of Wuhan Central Hospital said

Someone called and texted the Party secretary, Dean and four deputy deans of the Wuhan Central Hospital where Dr. Li Wenliang worked on Feb. 7 at 12:29 a.m. and 11:30 a.m. to verify the information, none of the six have answered their phones or returned messages.

When news of Li Wenliang's death was announced, he was greeted with outpouring of grief and respect. Many people called him an ordinary hero and expressed deep regret over his death. People don't want to see a person who told the truth die suddenly. He's not a hero, he's just a man like us, one netizen commented. He's doing what any of US could have done.

Around the time of Li's death, his colleagues were distraught. "there was no way to hold a memorial service, but we wanted to do something for his family, " said a colleague of Li's. Early on Feb. 7, the Hospital Union issued a notice to staff members to donate money to Li's family, but "we all prefer to give directly to the family rather than through the Union. "

A doctor in another department said Li Wenliang was the first of the center's hospital infection doctors to die, and there are still several doctors at the intensive-care unit.

Li's parents were also infected and had been hospitalized in a local hospital in Wuhan. They have been released and are still in Wuhan. His wife, who is nearly six months pregnant and uninfected, is in self-isolation at home with their five-year-old eldest son.

At 23:25 on February 6, the World Health Organization tweeted: "We are deeply saddened by the death of Dr. Li Wenliang, and we should all applaud his work on the new coronavirus epidemic. "

"The truth is all that matters. "

On the night of December 30,2019, Li Wenliang was a little livid.

He specifically told Wu Students, do not put their afternoon in the group sent screenshots to forward. Did Not expect to have a lot of people holding a chat record screen shot to cross-examine him: SARS really back?

Screenshot of Li Wenliang name and units were not coded, "south China seafood and fruit market confirmed 7 cases of SARS" below, with a piece of: "clinical pathogen screening results" detection report. This was enough to scare people who had experienced SARS, so many people ignored Li Wenliang's last few words: "The latest news is that coronavirus infection has been confirmed and virus typing is being carried out. " "Do not spread the word, let family members pay attention to prevent. ".

On the same day, the Wuhan Health Commission issued a red-headed document under the internal, said Wuhan appeared pneumonia of unknown cause, may be related to the south China Seafood Market.

Li's colleagues, and others at the Central Hospital, also received information about pneumonia of unknown origin, more verbal notifications to friends, relatives and colleagues to protect themselves. No one told more people in words like Li. "It's not allowed by law, " said a doctor at a central hospital.

Early on the morning of December 31,2019, Li Wenliang was called over for a talk by the leaders of the Wuhan Central Hospital. He was told that experts from the health commission were still having a meeting at 1:30 a.m. because of the incident, he later told Caixin, i thought, "If I admit I made a mistake, I'll be fine. ".

On January 1, Wuhan Police Notified Eight "rumour mongers" . Li did not know if he was one of them and later discovered that many of the eight "rumour-mongers" were doctors at a local hospital in Wuhan.

While Li was being "interviewed" , many doctors at Wuhan Central Hospital began to prepare protective materials. "It's impossible for a clinical frontline doctor to remind people around us without evidence that we are willing to trust him, " said a central hospital doctor who heard Li's warning and called on staff in his department to stock up urgently a box of N95 masks.

On January 3, Li Wenliang was called to the police station to sign a copy of the commandment. Li Wenliang, who has never encountered such a thing, could not help but worry that he was detained by the police station and influenced his promotion, so he cooperated with the procedure and signed.

Later, he was infected, lying in a hospital bed in the center of Caixin interview, said he did not want to go through the judicial channels to find the public security, "I am very afraid of trouble, justice is comfortable. "

In the eyes of his colleagues, he put his heart and soul into his work. Shortly after receiving the sermon, on January 8, he began seeing an ophthalmologist. But from January 10, he first appeared cough symptoms, did not pay attention to, still adhere to the line of work. On January 11, his temperature rose to 38.2 C, "and he realized there was a big problem. ". The CT results that day showed that Li Wenliang had multiple lung infections and ground-glass-like lesions.

He was accompanied by relatives caring for patients, two colleagues in his department, and even hospital officials who had verbally warned him not to spread "rumors. ". His boss, the head of the Ophthalmology Department, is still at the intensive-care unit.

Li sensed the first signs of the outbreak, but the virus spread much faster than he had expected.

A doctor at Wuhan Central Hospital said they began wearing masks at the end of December 2019, but "no one expected it to be so contagious. ". Around January 10, the hospital is the first group of hospital staff infection peak, "doctors went online to buy their own goggles and other protective materials. ".

For Li Wenliang, contagion did not hit the pause button. Around January 15, Li's parents were admitted to hospital. Although he had initiated quarantine, it had not stopped the spread of the virus.

In the process, Li has been hoping for an early diagnosis, which means he can have a more suitable bed and corresponding treatment. A local media source in Wuhan said Li Wenliang had three nucleic acid tests before and after, the first two were negative until the third was positive, "and there was a delay. ". It is understood that the situation in Wuhan at that time, doctors using nucleic acid test paper also need to queue up, only serious cases can be priority.

A Central Hospital doctor said, "the positive rate of nucleic acid test may only be 10% , some health care workers were discharged after infection, is also under isolation, still undiagnosed. "

According to the Beijing Youth Daily, Li's body temperature repeated around January 26, when he was already plugged into a straw, he could not get out of bed, defecate or urinate, could not communicate orally, and had to rely on typing, which made him dizzy after a long time. Li was better off around Jan. 20, his colleagues said, "but then it got worse quickly. ".

During the period, Li Wenliang gave several media interviews to narrate how he released the information.

At 10:00 am on January 23, Wuhan officially implemented a public transport system called "city closure" . Later, Zhou Xianwang, Wuhan's mayor, told reporters that 5m people had left the city before it was closed.

On January 27, nearly 1,000 new cases were confirmed in Wuhan. Zhou Xianwang admitted in an interview with CCTV, the local government information disclosure of coronavirus is not timely, I hope you understand. "As long as we get this epidemic under control, we [ are willing to ] thank the world by firing us. "

How many of the five million people who left did so because of information from eight "rumormongers" ? Li Wenliang a student sister is also a doctor, she said he is to see Li Wenliang in the group issued a reminder, just have a sense of prevention. "Many doctors in our hospital started to prepare protective materials after his warning, otherwise the infection would be more serious than now, " said Li Wenliang, who was described by a colleague as a "lifesaver. " The doctor came out of the intensive care unit, and the patient he treated this morning was a doctor who entered the unit without an N95 mask.

On January 28, Supreme People's Court posted an article about eight "rumor mongers" in Wuhan, saying that if the public had listened to the "rumor" and based on the fear of SARS, it may be a blessing that we are better able to prevent and control the new pneumonia today by wearing masks, applying strict disinfection and avoiding going back to the wildlife market.

Li Wenliang, who was already having difficulty breathing, also saw the article, telling a visiting Caixin reporter: "rehabilitation is not important, people see the truth is the most important. "

In early January, the Wuhan Central Hospital Epidemic Prevention and Control Leadership team selected medical staff on the front line, Li Wenliang wechat group in the third registration. After being admitted to hospital, he also wanted to recover after the first line.

Li Wenliang was finally diagnosed on Feb. 1, when he tweeted: "The dust has finally settled" with a dog's head Emoji.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Screenshot of Dr Li Wenliang's microblog

"Sacrifice to heaven, sacrifice to Earth, sacrifice to brother. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Wuhan Sakura Garden, image from the Internet

On the morning of February 7, Li's body was taken to the Hankou funeral home for cremation. The funeral home, located in a remote part of Wuhan, had to check passes along the way and had been closed off without relatives or friends to see him off. Wuhan funeral home and Wuhan Central Hospital on the same day of external contact telephone are difficult to get through.

As a doctor at Wuhan's Central Hospital, Li has always been an ordinary man. There are more than 4,000 people in both branches of Wuhan's Central Hospital, many of whom have never heard of him before. Sun Wenwu, a doctor at the same hospital, said he first met Dr. Li when the hospital punished a doctor who told the truth in early January.

Li Wenliang once said that his attitude towards life is: Life Without examination is not worth living, and I hope everyone can realize their value.

A colleague familiar with Li Wenliang said, Li Wenliang optimistic, loyal, very good care of people, "he is that kind of person, by the drip of grace, will Yongquan reported. ".

"My family was taken care of by him all the way to Bali, " said a co-worker who was unable to travel because of his shift schedule. According to him, Li Wenliang is "a free English translator for everyone, and he also knows some Japanese, which comes in handy when traveling. "

Another colleague said, in daily work, Li Wenliang is a careful, thoughtful doctor, on the patient's disease prognosis, pay attention to things are very detailed account.

According to people around him, he also like an ordinary "85" youth, Love Star, watching TV, like to watch cars, electronic products review; often want to eat at midnight, fried chicken, instant noodles, Japanese food... . For him, the food was "too tempting" . He also complained about not wanting to go to work, counting down the days a week before the holidays.

Once he strolls the supermarket, saw the car centimeter son one catty 158 yuan, laments really can not afford to eat. He was excited to retweet the winning lottery ticket and give it to Cherubic. Someone carefully read his previous tweets, most of which were retweets of the lottery.

Li also often showed warmth and blood in his character, colleagues said. During the April 2013 earthquake in Ya'an, he made two donations, both on Weibo. On December 28,2019, he reposted the news that Dr. Yang Wen of Beijing Civil Aviation General Hospital had been killed, expressing sadness and anger.

He has a happy family, and his wife, a doctor at Aier Eye Hospital Group Company Limited, is pregnant for nearly six months and is expected to give birth in July. Their eldest son is five years old. His wechat profile picture is the Crayon family of four. On Nov. 9,2019, he retweeted the beauty of the Great Wall in autumn, saying when he and his son could experience it.

On Weibo, Li Wenliang wrote his wish for 2020: to be a simple person for the new year, to see the world clearly but not to leave traces in his heart, and to keep enough common sense.

A journalist who interviewed Li Wenliang wrote an article after his death, "we lost a kind and magnanimous interviewee last night. ". She was one of the first journalists to interview Li Wenliang.

At that time, Li Wenliang was lying in the intensive care unit, and the interview was finished by typing, "He was a very slow typist, answering only a few words at a time, and he needed a rest after communicating for a while. It was not easy for him to give interviews at that time, " the reporter recalled to Caijing.

But even so, Li's account was unsparing. "I saw the interview and I said 'Fang, ' " he said, speaking on the condition of anonymity to protect him. "If you look for someone, you can find them. " She also coded his medical records, disciplinary papers, and hospital signs, but then saw Li Wenliang appear in other reports under his real name.

The reporters kept in touch with Li Wenliang one after another. In a 9 a.m. conversation on Jan. 27, she asked Li how many pills he was taking each day. Li responded "a lot, " and then asked him to be more specific. "I don't have the energy, " he said.

A doctor friend familiar with Li said that the last conversation he had with Li on Wechat was when Li said, "there is still hope for Wuhan, and we expect to basically control the situation by the end of February. " Li also reminded him to be careful when facing patients with fever, if we don't protect them, we'RE GONNA die. They arranged to have a drink together when Li Wenliang got well.

"If I had a chance to see him sober yesterday, I would have told him first, you can rest assured, what you are worried about is nothing, you have people in your house to take care of you; second, you take a rest, change the brothers on, the brothers have been on, don't put out the virus I'm sorry for your sacrifice, we have our lives to carry it out to the end! Third, the scheduled dinner, visual assessment is too late, if we have to sacrifice these people, that is fine, while not far away, on the spot ！! If we live, we'll drink wine and sacrifice to our brothers every year."

On the morning of February 7, Li Wenliang's doctor friend set up a mobile phone calendar: every year from now on February 6, it is a day for "Li Wenliang's sacrifice, " "every year around February 6, EAT! " He is also a doctor, in Wuhan, "before the city" to the hospital issued a letter of request: "ready to call and dispatch, regardless of life and death, regardless of remuneration

When a colleague of Li's learned of his death, he recalled the details of his time with him in the circle of friends: You are the cutest colleague in my eyes. You speak slowly, never loudly or in a hurry. You never say no to a shift change, and no matter what they say, you always say, "okay. ". I can't believe you're gone.

February 7,2020 -- AM session, "Dr. Li Wenliang of Wuhan Central Hospital died of COVID-19 pneumonia in the fight against the epidemic. He was given all-out treatment. The National Health Commission expressed deep condolences and sincere condolences to the family of Dr. Li Wenliang, " the NHCHC said in a statement on its website

At the Joint Defense and Joint Control Mechanism Press Conference of the State Council held on February 7, song Shuli, a spokesman for the National Health and Human Services Commission, said: "Dr Li Wenliang died of COVID-19 pneumonia in the fight against the epidemic. The Commission expressed deep condolences and sincere condolences to Dr Li's family. " She added: At present, the fight against the epidemic is in a critical period, the situation of prevention and control is still severe and complex, the whole society needs to care more about medical personnel.

That morning, hubei Provincial Health Commission official website released news: "learned that Wuhan Central Hospital Ophthalmologist Li Wenliang in the fight against the epidemic in the unfortunate infection of new pneumonia, died after all efforts to rescue ineffective. ". The Provincial Health Commission expressed deep condolences to Dr. Li Wenliang and sincere condolences to his family."

On the morning of February 7th, "Dr. Li Wenliang, of Wuhan Central Hospital, died from a new type of pneumonia after intensive rescue, " said a notice posted on the official website of the Wuhan Municipal Government. We're very sorry for your loss. Very sorry! Pay Tribute to him for sticking to the frontline in fighting the epidemic and express sincere condolences to his family."

That morning, the official website of the Government of the People's Republic of China reprinted the deep condolences of the Provincial Health Commission and the tribute of the Wuhan Municipal Government.

In addition, according to a report by the Hubei Radio, television and financial media, after an application by the Central Hospital of Wuhan, the Wuhan Municipal Bureau of People's Social Welfare confirmed on February 7 that, li Wenliang as a medical staff in the fight against COVID-19 pneumonia in the work of the unfortunate infection and died after rescue invalid, identified as industrial injury. According to accounting, Li Wenliang industrial injury insurance benefits are as follows: one-time death benefits 785,020 yuan, funeral benefits 36,834 yuan.

At a little after 9 pm on February 7, a whistle sounded outside Wuhan's Central Hospital, accompanied by shouts of "Go Wuhan! " . "I don't know Dr. Li, but I felt I had to come, " said a tearful 50-year-old resident of the hospital who was interviewed by CCTV. "I wanted to send a bunch of flowers, but they weren't for sale. "

But the hospital outpatient building is still full of flowers, mostly yellow and white chrysanthemums, "thank you for your courage, " is the most flowers on the eulogy.
